For, thinking himself better learned then his Mt, he went an ase further, denyinge damneably y· reall presence of the body and blood of our Saviour in the blessed sacrement of the altar. Wherfore the grave prelate and zelous pastor, lyke a valiant champion (that never could he tyred), set upon this ravening woolfe with five weapons, which were five bookes most dilligently penned and clerkly collected, well stuffed with evident Scriptures and censures of holy fathers», both in their learned works and also in their generall conusens, where lawfully assembled they have decreed such things as are expedient for the maintenance of the truth, there representing our mother the Church.
